Overview

The most recent Master Property File from the city of Milwaukee has 160,068 records, compared with 161,038 in 2014. The total count for 2024 includes 100,353 single family homes.

Of that group, there are 98,354 single-family properties for which the same tax ID exists both in the most recent file and in 2014. Those homes saw their value change by a total of $10,659,613,018 over that period, with an average change of $108,380 and a median change of $100,300.
